[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The critical path is the sequence of activities in a project that has no slack time, meaning there is no margin for error when performing these activities.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Since the critical path has no slack, there is no margin for error when performing the activities along its route.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Activities on the critical path must be completed on schedule to avoid delay, and any delay in these activities pushes all subsequent critical path activities forward.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The late start pushes all subsequent critical path activities forward, forcing them to be late, too, if there is no slack.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The critical path can be identified using the Critical Path Method (CPM), which analyzes the paths among the milestones of a project to show the minimum amount of time to complete the project and reveals the most critical activities.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Analyzing the paths among the milestones of a project in this way is called the Critical Path Method (CPM). The paths can show us the minimum amount of time it will take to complete the project, given our estimates of each activity's duration. Moreover, CPM reveals those activities that are most critical to completing the project on time.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "In the bar chart shown in Figure 3.4, the critical path activities are represented by bars composed of asterisks.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Figure 3.4 is a bar chart that shows some software development project activities, including information about the early and late start dates; this chart is typical of those produced by automated project management tools. The horizontal bars represent the duration of each activity; those bars composed of asterisks indicate the critical path.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    }
]

[
    {
        "role": "sentence",
        "segment": "The two components used to describe a preferred work style are the way in which your thoughts are communicated and ideas gathered, and the degree to which your emotions affect decision making.",
        "citations": [
