[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The personnel roles actively involved during the System Testing phase include professional testers, analysts, system designers, configuration management specialists, and users.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The testers are familiar not only with the system specification, but also with testing methods and tools. Professional testers organize and run the tests. They are involved from the beginning, designing test plans and test cases as the project progresses.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Because the testers may not be as well-versed in the particulars of the requirements as those who wrote them, the test team includes additional people who are familiar with the requirements. Analysts who were involved in the original requirements definition and specification are useful in testing because they understand the problem as defined by the customer.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "System designers add the perspective of intent to the test team. The designers understand what we proposed as a solution, as well as the solution's constraints.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Because tests and test cases are tied directly to requirements and design, a configuration management representative is on the test team.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Finally, the test team includes users. They are best qualified to evaluate issues dealing with appropriateness of audience, ease of use, and other human factors.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Programmers are generally not involved in system testing because they are too familiar with the implementation and may have difficulty recognizing differences between implementation and required function or performance.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Often, no programmers from the project are involved in system testing; they are too familiar with the implementation's structure and intention, and they may have difficulty recognizing the differences between implementation and required function or performance.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    }
]

[
